Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar Condensed ExtraLight' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar Cond ExtLt' (NID 1).

Pass

Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Light Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-Condensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-Condensed', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-Condensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar Condensed' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar Cond' (NID 1).

Pass

MS NID 6

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedBold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Blk Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedBlack.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedBlack', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Blk Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-CondensedBlack.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar Condensed Black' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar Cond Blk' (NID 1).
